Path: Highlights
Content:
This week brings a shiny new 
``explore config``
 command, some improved 
``explore regex``
 and 
``explore``
 UI, and HTTP pooling (amazing that our little shell does 
this
!).
Also, MCP is included in all builds by default going forward! And hints can be user-disabled without resorting to hacky theme changes!
—ЩRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2025-12-19-twin0330.mdЩ@ed3dd171e0878a40f2d350715788ecd9c07256ca75dd98cecf2015c78b460ed8Щ"title: 'This week in Nushell #330'‘§NushellЪ	@reubeno:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17203] updated reedline to the latest commit (#17203)
@sgvictorino:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17200] made MCP server interruptible (#17200)
@fdncred:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17199] fixed the mcp ctrl-c bug (#17199)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17197] updated reedline to the latest commit (#17197)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17187] added quick reference panel to 
``explore regex``
 command (#17187)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17183] updated uutils to 0.5.0 (#17183)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17181] refactored 
``explore``
 family of commands for better understanding and maintenance (#17181)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17176] added syntax highlighting to 
``explore config``
 (#17176)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17172] cleaned up explore a bit (#17172)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17170] added search capability to 
``explore config``
 command (#17170)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17169] updated match count when test text changes (#17169)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17168] updated doc config (#17168)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17148] added agents.md to help LLMs (#17148)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17147] added new command: 
``explore config``
 TUI (#17147)
@app/dependabot:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17195] bumped procfs from 0.17.0 to 0.18.0 (#17195)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17194] bumped strum from 0.26.3 to 0.27.2 (#17194)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17193] bumped winreg from 0.52.0 to 0.55.0 (#17193)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17192] bumped bytes from 1.10.0 to 1.11.0 (#17192)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17191] bumped http from 1.3.1 to 1.4.0 (#17191)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17190] bumped actions/upload-artifact from 5 to 6 (#17190)
@NotTheDr01ds:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17186] added CARGO
*
 and RUSTUP
*
 environment variables back to test environment (#17186)
@WindSoilder:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17185] made 
``mv/cp/du *``
 not match dotfiles by default (#17185)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17177] added http pool cmd (#17177)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17157] enabled http commands to use builtin connection pool (#17157)
@andrewgazelka:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17163] added stderr redirection BAD/GOOD examples to mcp instructions (#17163)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17153] added string interpolation syntax to mcp instructions (#17153)
@splintersuidman:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17156] added configuration option for showing hints (#17156)
@blindFS:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17152] fixed parser overflow by using 
``checked_sub``
 in 
``parse_range``
 (#17152)
@ayax79:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17151] added mcp to default and all features (#17151)
@blackhat-hemsworth:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17134] improved error message for rm Os errors (#17134)
